articles.description:
According to BlockBeats news on March 26th, as monitored by @ai_9684xtpa, two addresses were the first to buy DAO Maker's MEME project PUNDU, and within only 40 minutes, they had already made a profit of 31,113 SOL, worth $5.94 million. The two addresses' operations were highly consistent and are suspected to belong to the same person:

Address 1: Spent 17,285 SOL to buy 86.34 million PUNDU at a cost of 0.03803, and subsequently sold in batches for a profit of $4.08 million;

Address 2: Spent 17,283 SOL to buy 51.74 million PUNDU at a cost of 0.06346, and sold in batches for a total profit of $1.86 million.
